Veteran Student Life

• Differences between the VA’s Education Benefit Programs;

The Office of Veteran Student Life in the Adele H. Stamp Student Union offers a hub of resources that serves veterans and military connected students, staff, and faculty on campus, with programs including; Veterans- specific New Student Orientation, Transition Assistance, Veteran-focused Career and Networking events, as well as Veteran- centered Campus Events and Programs and a Veteran Center on Campus.

The Office of the University Registrar’s Veteran Certifications Services houses the University of Maryland’s School Certifying Officials (SCOs). These are the individuals who communicate information about your enrollment at the University of Maryland to the U.S. Department of Veterans Affairs so they may process your VA Education Benefits.

